      "content": "Thanks for this. It sounds really professional. One thing though—I'm worried that mentioning it was just a \"10-participant pilot\" in the first sentence might get us rejected immediately by Nature reviewers. They're usually pretty harsh on small sample sizes. \n\nHow can we rephrase or frame the methodology section of the abstract so it focuses more on the robustness and the significance of the data collected, without sounding like it's just a tiny preliminary test?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
